reviewText: I remember watching this show on MTV when it first came on.  Not a bad show if I say so myself.  You know what's funny? Diggy became the "big" rapper in the family but not JoJo? Hm.
Title: Run's House - The Complete Seasons 1 & 2

reviewText: Pretty damn funny, they seem like a very close family.  I died laughing when Russy was embarrassed that his dad was picking him up from the Bus Stop in a $250,000 Phantom. So Run shows up the next day in the same ride wearing a Gorilla Suit.  And watching Russy destroy his game boys never gets old.  This is one of the best reality shows I've seen. And Run hiding his wifes burgers from Wendy's because he wanted her to go on a diet, and her spending half the episode looking for them LOL.
Title: Run's House - The Complete Seasons 1 & 2

reviewText: Run's House! I really hate that this isn't on TV anymore. It's nice to see an African American family on a reality show, and they aren't ghetto. I really miss this show!
Title: Run's House - The Complete Seasons 1 & 2

reviewText: I used to watch Run's House like everyday of my life. I loved the family interaction. I can tell that Rev. Run really loves his family. Comedy mixed with real parenting. Way to go Run.
Title: Run's House - The Complete Seasons 1 & 2

reviewText: Great collection of DVDs from one of the nicer reality tv shows in history. This family reminds me of a mixture of the Cosby Show, with a Hip Hop flavor.  Each segment ends on a positive note. Rev Run is the head of household and his kids are typical teens and pre-teens. Very funny and family-friendly.
Title: Run's House - The Complete Seasons 1 & 2
